"Pours a deep brown but appears tar black, producing 2.5 fingers of dark mocha, moderately lasting, frothy head that leaves little lace. Nose is dark roasted malt, coffee with hints of cocoa, toffee & dark fruit. Taste is dark bitter coffee, dark malts with roast & burnt notes, dark chocolate, dark fruits, smoke & faint anise. A pleasant but delicate bitter quality develops following mid-sip, increasing through the finish & balancing with sweet in the initial aftertaste but soon becoming dominant. Aftertaste is smoky bitter chocolate & roast. Mouthfeel is medium-heavy bodied, low-moderate carbonation, creamy, smooth & somewhat chewy."
"Draft poured pint. This is a low ABV session stout that does exactly what it says on the tin (bottle/tapline etc). Dark brown to red in color, with a thin frothy head. Has a thin mouthfeel as expected. Mild coffee notes, with little of the milk sugars coming through. Easy drinking. Good for what it is."
