"Not your usual Stone beer! I was expecting espresso to a certain extent, but what I got was more of a latte: it's creamy, coffee-like, cocoa-ish, milk chocolatey, and gently nutty with an edge of sweetish dark caramel that's almost like a bit of candy-ish almost-burnt sugar. There's some dark malt acidity to it, but not much, and the bitterness level is restrained to what I'd call moderate. There's just enough to balance it in combination with the soft roasty dryness. It's easily drinkable, and I guess it should be at just 4.2% abv. A tasty treat that goes down to easily and leaves you wondering where your beer went."
