"Single 12 oz. bottle poured into a tulip. Very dark essentially pitch black brew with a thin layer of rich tan creamy bubbles on top and around the sides of the glass. Nose is chocolate and coffee in approximately equal measure, with some toffee notes as well. Interesting on the palate ... There is plenty of chocolate but also dry roasted coffee bean to cut much of the sweetness along with some distinct dark roasted barley notes, chocolate malt all the way. Silky smooth and light bodied with a notably dry roasted finish with little residual sweetness. I probably would not be able to pick this out as a clear milk stout. As everyone says its a diversion for Stone and probably a worthwhile pick-up for the English stout lover. I find myself yearning for just a touch more sweetness."
