"Overall this was OK. I think the beer should just be called ""Stone Coffee Stout"" instead, but that's just me. I didn't find this one to be too creamy or anything like that. I keep mentioning the bitterness, but it was on the verge of being too much. I wish Stone listed the IBUs on their website. At 4.2% abv, you could have a few of these with your pals and not get wrecked. So for a low abv beer, this is an absolute winner. Coroando's Blue Ridge Coffee Stout beats this one hands down for me. Try that one if you can find it. I'll stick with Young's Double Chocolate Stout (my favorite beer) and Left Hand's Milk Stout Nitro if I'm looking to drink a beer in this style as well."
