"Pours deep black with a thick creamy darker tan head. The head dissipates pretty quickly, leaving some light soapy lacing. The aroma is a nice combination of the lactic sweetness, the coffee and a slight roasted malt astringency. The taste is not a punch in the mouth, as the style could be, but a subtle balancing of all the flavors in a lower ABV body. It really comes in to its own as it warms to about 50F. The body is lighter, as a milk stout should be, with a nice silky quality to it. A session-able and flavorful stout."
"Overall:  Decent flavor, but thin and watery.  This would be a good light session beer if you wanted more flavor from a light beer, but if you're used to full-bodied stouts this will not satisfy you."
