"Mouthfeel is pretty good, lighter bodied than I expected.  Modestly carbonated providing a nice smooth feel, not quite ""silky"" but nice.  Flavors mesh together nicely, has a long lingering flavor despite the light feel ing the tongue.  Not overly drinkable, for a low alcohol beer, it's more of a sipper, but kudos on the big flavor for a a beer that's badly over 4% ABV.  Overall a pretty good beer, but I was expecting a little more, It tasted more what I'd expect if they did a smoked porter series brewed over coffee beans.  Also, really expensive for a low alcohol six pack.  Still a good beer though, glad I got to try it."
