"12 ounce bottle into pint glass, best before 12/23/2014. Pours fairly pitch black color with a 2 finger dense tan head with great retention, that reduces to a nice cap that lasts. Dense soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a moderate amount of streaming carbonation retaining the head. Aromas of milk chocolate, cocoa, coffee, roasted malt, dark bread, cream, toast, light char, and roasted earthiness. Very nice aromas with good balance and complexity of roasted malt, coffee, and lactose notes; with good strength. Taste of milk chocolate, cocoa, coffee, roasted malt, toast, dark bread, cream, light char, and roasted earthiness. Light amount of roasted bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of milk chocolate, cocoa, coffee, roast, dark bread, toast, cream, and roasted earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Very nice complexity and robustness of roasted malt, coffee, and lactose flavors; with a good roasted bitterness/sweetness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a very smooth and moderately silky/creamy mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with zero warming present after the finish as expected of 4.2%. Overall this is a very nice session milk stout! All around good complexity and robustness of roasted malt, coffee, and lactose flavors; and very smooth to drink. A very enjoyable offering."
