"Bottle from Tipples. Excited to try this one at only 4.2% ABV. Pours darn brown to black with a one finger khaki creamy head. Big earthy roasted coffee bean aroma, sweet lactose and some light chocolateyness. Flavor is earthy and spicy coffee, some chocolate sweetness of you look for it, very light flavors but the bold coffee sits on the palate a while after. Some metallic notes. On the thinner side, though that is expected at the ABV, with high carbonation. This seems to need a bit more beef, and there seems to be room to do a at the low ABV. As is, pretty flavorful given the almost session strength. But creaminess would add a lot here. A good beer overall that seems to hit what it is going for: coffee and easy drinking."
