"I'm a big fan of Stone Brewing and a stout beer snob, a ""stob"" if you will.  Stone's Imperial Russian is utterly sublime so it was with great anticipation that I tried their Coffee Milk Stout.  After the first few sips I just sat the glass down and scratched my head then went and looked at the bottle again since what just went in my mouth wasn't a milk stout, it just didn't have the quintessential traits of beers that define that category.  It was a fairly drinkable Irish stout with a very faint whiff of coffee but it most definitely was not a milk stout.  Perhaps they passed a bag of lactose over the brew kettle but I think they forgot to add any of its contents.  I think Mr. Gallagher needs to return to the U.K. and continue his training before damaging Stone's reputation any further."
