"As a coffee fiend, I was excited to try Stone's take on the style. Poured a 12 oz bottle into a nonic pint glass, and it was beautfull: dark black with a sizable mocha head. The head stayed at about a half-finger's width until it was gone and provided nice lacing. The aroma was by far the best thing about the beer. It smelled exactly like a perfectly roasted cup of coffee with subtle hints of cocoa (noticed this after the beer warmed a bit). After the aroma, though, the taste did not live up to the nose. There was a distinct charcoal taste that I felt did not mesh well with the roasted coffee and sweet lactose flavors. It did meld a bit better as it warmed, but not enough to redeem it. The mouthfeel was decent with all the trappings of a standard milk stout. Overall, not a bad beer, but not particularly good either."
""
""
""
"The aroma is what it is. Coffee and milk. Lactose, light char leads the flavor profile. With very little flavor coming through. I wanted so much more from this beer. But I didn't get big coffee flavor, or dark chocolate. It's very smooth. I just wanted an aggressive beer. Like from most Stone beer's. The worst Stone brew by far."
